	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Oct 5th 9:52 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've never seen another one on E'ci.&nbsp;&nbsp;I might not have the only one, but there can't be many if there are others.  The camps for this take forever.<br><br>On the bright side, it has better stats than most mid-lvl Robes.  The +mana and +resists are fairly rare as far as &lt; lvl 50 robes go.<br><br>If you want to camp it (good luck) you have to clear the entire Shadow island in TS for hours, days, or even weeks for the Disgraced Shadow.  I hunted there several times in multi-hour sessions with my Mage, plvled my Wizard for 2 levels there, and cleared it several times for loot.  I never saw the Disgraced Shadow once in what I estimate to be ~40 hrs of camping.  A guildmate gave me the Book of Sorcery.<br><br>The Powerful Thought Leech is the first spawn on the left, inside the first cave to the left of MS (as you zone into ML from MS).  Just kill the left spawn repeatedly until it pops the PTL.  I got very lucky and spawned him as the 4th cycle.<br><br>Coterie Gladiator, another treat.  He spawns at Bedlavar's Coterie camp, first one North of Katta along the West zone wall.  The Gladiator specifically spawn to the right of the ramp, in front of Bedlavar's house (the one against the West wall).  The named Coterie for the Beastlord BP also spawns in the exact same spot.  It took me 8hrs to spawn the Gladiator the first time, and since then I have plvld for about 16 more hours at the same camp and haven't seen Gladiator once.<br><br>I don't think I would part with this robe for any less than 12k, given the difficulty to attain it and the unique look, not to mention the RARITY of it.  It's quite a status symbol to have people always clicking on you going &quot;what's that robe?&quot;<br>&nbsp;<br>kill_entity($mob) or die "LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...";</td></tr>
